{
  "name": "Inspiring Leader",
  "type": "feat",
  "img": "icons/magic/symbols/mask-metal-silver-white.webp",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>Category: General </p><p>Prerequisite: Charisma 15+ </p><p>You can spend 10 minutes inspiring your companions, shoring up their resolve to fight.</p><p> When you do so, choose up to six friendly creatures (which can include yourself) within 30 feet of you who can see or hear you and who can understand you.</p><p> Each creature can gain temporary hit points and temporary chakra points equal to your Proficiency bonus + your Charisma ability score.</p><p> Also, each creature gains two Leader Die, which are d4s.</p><p> A creature can spend one Leader Die when they make an attack roll, skill check, initiative, or saving throw, no more than once per roll.</p><p> A creature can gain the benefits of this feat no more than once per rest.</p><p></p>",
